default7.   
defaultEducation reflects wider social and economic conditions. We are at a point 
defaultin time when the power of the working classes economically and socially is diminishing while the power of the elites has increased
default, 
default and the middle classes are struggling to maintain their position in  society. There is also a troubling growth in the social distance between the classes. When I was growing up as a working class child in the 50s and 60s, my educational success rested par
defaulttly on the empathy and kindness of the parents of my middle class classmates who invited me to complete my homework in houses with space and places to concentrate. Today, the middle class parents I interviewed talk of  mistrust and even fear of the white w
defaultorking classes: 
default              
defaultHe doesn’t bring these children home but at least he knows where they come from
default. 
